      <bioghist id="ref7">
         <head>Biographical/Historical Sketch</head>
         <p>A solar physicist, Wilcox worked around the world studying the influence of solar magnetism on global weather patterns. A professor at Stanford University from 1971 to his death in 1983, he was also director of the Stanford Solar Observatory, 1973-1983.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="ref8">
         <head>Description of the Collection</head>
         <p>Correspondence, astrophysics papers, refereeing reports, lecture notes, travel records, reprints, research notes, films, and biographical materials, largely relating to his research and teaching.</p>
      </scopecontent>
